Subject: [PATCH] lib:replace Query libbsd.pc before bsd syslib checks

Samba wired the bsd syslib without ever reading libbsd.pc, so Cflags from the
.pc (extra -I/-isystem on multilib or similar layouts) never reached uselib
BSD.

Before those bsd syslib checks, run a non-mandatory pkg-config query for libbsd
so libbsd.pc can populate CFLAGS_BSD, INCLUDES_BSD, and LIB_BSD when the .pc is
installed and visible to pkg-config.

global_define=False because True also writes a HAVE_* line into config.h when
pkg-config succeeds; this call should only copy libbsd.pc flags into the build
environment, not add a HAVE_* that exists only because this pkg-config step
succeeded.

--- a/lib/replace/wscript
+++ b/lib/replace/wscript
@@ -441,6 +441,12 @@
 
     conf.CHECK_FUNCS('dirname basename')
 
+    conf.check_cfg(package='libbsd', args='--cflags --libs',
+                   msg='Checking for libbsd via pkg-config',
+                   uselib_store='BSD',
+                   mandatory=False,
+                   global_define=False)
+
     strlcpy_in_bsd = False
 
     # libbsd on some platforms provides strlcpy and strlcat
